One question before committee members then is whether Gen. Kelly will check the agency’s worst practices or only make them worse.
Courtesy photoAs the former head of U.S. Southern Command under President Obama, Gen. Kelly was known for his hawkish and alarmist stances on border security.
His limited comments before Congress on border enforcement have solely framed Southwest border communities — my community — as a threat to national security.
Six were people standing on Mexican soil — including three teenagers — when shot and killed by Border Patrol agents standing in the United States.
Vicki B. Gaubeca is director of the ACLU of New Mexico’s Regional Center for Border Rights.